      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC2e7588502590100586bbfed1f18860d2"></a>Inspection of the gear selector drum
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e15675"> </a>Use a gauge to measure the clearance between fork pin and the slot on the selector drum.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e15677"> </a>If the service limit is exceeded, determine which part must be replaced by comparing these dimensions with those of new components
            (<a href="50500.html#DUCcafc4150295a100581759858899a76d2">Gearbox</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e15682"> </a>Also check the wear on the drum support pins; these must not show any signs of scoring, burrs, or deformation.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e15684"> </a>Turn the drum in the crankcase to establish the extent of radial play. If play is excessive, change whichever part is most
            worn.
         </div>
      </div>
